    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1970-09-23T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1970-09-23T10:00:00-05:00" n="319"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d319">
                <head>319. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Embassy in Israel</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d319fn1">Source: National Archives, <gloss
                            target="#t_RG1">RG</gloss> 59, Central Files 1970–73, AV 12. Secret;
                        Immediate. It was repeated to Amman (Immediate), Beirut, Bonn, Bern, London,
                        and Geneva.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Tel Aviv</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1970-09-23T15:00:00+00:00">September 23, 1970,
                        1500Z</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5318. Subj: Hijacking Hostages.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Foreign Ministry (Baron) has asked us make urgent suggestion that
                        Government of Jordan be urged to include release of hijacking hostages as
                        part of any settlement made with fedayeen. Baron noted <gloss
                            target="#t_GOJ1">GOJ</gloss> said to be holding number of important
                        fedayeen prisoners, and should not let them go without getting hostages
                        out.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Since, in a sense, hijacking and hostage situation was immediate cause of
                            <gloss target="#t_GOJ1">GOJ</gloss>–fedayeen blowup, there would
                        certainly seem to be logic in Israeli idea that settlement of hostages
                        should be part of settlement of blowup. In this connection, we note Israeli
                        radio broadcast noon today said four fedayeen leaders had been released by
                        Jordanian Army.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>Zurhellen</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
